00:09:56.399 --> 00:10:02.770
really exploded in the mid-1990's when something
called functional magnetic resonance imaging

00:10:02.770 --> 00:10:09.529
became widely available. And before that fields
of psychologies did behavioral studies but

00:10:09.529 --> 00:10:13.850
it was hard to get a good impression or a
good idea, a concrete idea, of exactly what

00:10:13.850 --> 00:10:17.330
was going on because we couldn't see into
people's heads.

00:10:17.330 --> 00:10:21.520
And functional magnetic resonance imaging
or FMRI allows scientists in a way to see

00:10:21.520 --> 00:10:25.820
into people's heads because it provides a
3-D picture not only of the structure of the

00:10:25.820 --> 00:10:30.960
brain but of what parts of the brain are currently
active, as you can see here by the yellow

00:10:30.960 --> 00:10:36.850
